com.ibm.team.process.common

Interface IModifyElement


  • public interface IModifyElement
    Represents the modify-element child of a configuration-data-delta element.
    Since:
    4.0.4

    • Method Summary

      Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      java.util.List<IProcessConfigurationElement> getPath()
      Get the list of IProcessConfigurationElement that describe where in the configuration-data tree this addition should take place.
      java.util.List<IRemoveAttribute> getRemoveAttributes()
      Get the list of IRemoveAttribute that describe the attribute removals to be performed on the element specified by the path.
      java.util.List<ISetAttribute> getSetAttributes()
      Get the list of ISetAttribute that describe the attribute modifications to be performed on the element specified by the path.
      ISetText getSetText()
      Get the ISetText that describes a modification to the text value of the element specified by the path or null if no set-text was specified.

    • Method Detail

      • getPath

        java.util.List<IProcessConfigurationElement> getPath()
        Get the list of IProcessConfigurationElement that describe where in the configuration-data tree this addition should take place.
        Returns:
        List of IProcessConfigurationElement, may be empty but not null.

      • getSetAttributes

        java.util.List<ISetAttribute> getSetAttributes()
        Get the list of ISetAttribute that describe the attribute modifications to be performed on the element specified by the path. The list might be empty but should never be null.
        Returns:
        List of ISetAttribute, may be empty but not null.

      • getRemoveAttributes

        java.util.List<IRemoveAttribute> getRemoveAttributes()
        Get the list of IRemoveAttribute that describe the attribute removals to be performed on the element specified by the path. The list might be empty but should never be null.
        Returns:
        List of IRemoveAttribute, may be empty but not null.

      • getSetText

        ISetText getSetText()
        Get the ISetText that describes a modification to the text value of the element specified by the path or null if no set-text was specified.
        Returns:
        ISetText or null if no set-text was specified.
